{
  "texts": [
    "The model's performance was sensitive to the review length due to the number of features considered by the classifier.",
    "The lack of real-life datasets impeded the fake review classification in the Amazon reviews dataset, therefore, to make use of the abundance of unlabeled datasets it is needed to employ semi-supervised and unsupervised learning approaches.",
    "Although in the literature many studies have claimed to build a publicly available largescale dataset.",
    "The second dataset used in this project constitutes of computer-generated reviews labelled fake and unfiltered Amazon reviews labelled original which might have fake reviews initially.",
    "The SVM technique resulted in 88% accuracy, while the merged subsets of the two datasets yielded 84% accuracy.The goal in the future is to find a dataset that reflects real-life consumer fake reviews."
  ]
}